SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: QUAD CITIES CHAMBER OF COMMERCE IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(6) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND COMPARABLE STATE LAW. AS OF JUNE 30, 2023, MANAGEMENT IS NOT AWARE OF ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AND RELATED TAX BENEFITS WHICH WOULD BE MATERIAL TO THE COMBINED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION FILES U.S FEDERAL AND STATE OF ILLINOIS (IF APPLICABLE) INFORMATION RETURNS WHICH FOR FISCAL YEARS SUBSEQUENT TO 2019 ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAXING AUTHORITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE QUAD CITIES CHAMBER OF COMMERCE IS A COMBINED CHAMBER OF COMMERCE, ECONOMIC, AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT ORGANIZATION SERVING THE GREATER QUAD CITIES REGION. THE QUAD CITIES CHAMBER OF COMMERCE'S MISSION IS TO STRENGTHEN AND ENHANCE THE BUSINESS ENVIRONMENT, REPRESENT THE INTERESTS OF MEMBERS, AND FOSTER BALANCED GROWTH IN THE QUAD CITIES REGION.
THE CHAMBER RECEIVED FUNDING AND BEGAN DEVELOPING A MULTI-COHORT GENERATION NEXT PROGRAM TO ACQUAINT AND PREPARE UP AND COMING LEADERS FOR CIVIC AND COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT.
FORM 990 WAS REVIWED AND APPROVED BY THE AUDIT COMMITTEE AND IT WAS PROVIDED TO ALL THE BOARD MEMBERS PRIOR TO ITS FILING WITH THE IRS.

THE COMPLETION OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS MONITORED BY THE QUAD CITIES CHAMBER OF COMMERCE EXECUTIVE SERVICES MANAGER. THE CEO REVIEWS THE COMPLETED CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS. CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS ARE REQUIRED TO BE COMPLETED ANNUALLY.

THE CEO'S SALARY IS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD CHAIR AND THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE AND IT IS DOCUMENTED IN AN EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT. A COMPARABILITY STUDY WITH THE AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE EXECUTIVES IS USED TO DETERMINE COMPENSATION FOR THE CEO.

THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC AT ITS PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS. THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE IN ACCORDANCE WITH POLICY AND PROCEDURES SET FORTH BY ITS BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
KERRY SMITH DEPARTED THE ORGANIZATION AS VP OF FINANCE IN APRIL OF 2023. BRIETTA COLLIER ASSUMED THE POSITION AS VP OF FINANCE IN APRIL OF 2023.
